  "classification": "Role",
  "reasoning": "Butterfly is a rigid property because an instance cannot cease to be a butterfly without ceasing to exist (biological essence). It supplies its own identity conditions (IC) to distinguish one butterfly from another and defines a whole organism with intrinsic boundaries, making it unifying."
