{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "+R",
    "identity": "+I",
    "own_identity": "+O",
    "unity": "+U",
    "dependence": "-D"
  },
  "classification": "Natural Kind",
  "reasoning": "Person is rigid (+R) because if an entity is a Person, it cannot cease to be a Person without ceasing to exist. It supplies its own identity conditions (+O, +I) allowing us to distinguish one person from another over time and space. It possesses unity (+U) as it represents a functional whole rather than a mere sum of parts, and is generally considered independent (-D) as it does not require the existence of another specific entity to exist (unlike a role like 'Student')."
}

